The paper deals with lower bounds for graph problems in the LOCAL model, which is a distributed computing model. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category. The paper also focuses on fundamental graph problems such as vertex cover, dominating set, and matching, which fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also uses graph theory concepts such as maximal independent sets and maximal matchings, which are part of cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.NE (Networks and Economics).
